  "killed_early_reason": "Wandering confirmed on the 50k-200k trajectory (success 92->100->50->25%); per the slice rules (kill early if wandering; do not grind; R-PPL-01 capacity) the run was stopped at ~240k rather than spending the full 900k budget on a demonstrably unstable optimisation. Nothing frozen; manifest not written; reference not lowered.",
  "intervention": "reasonable-effort stabilization (2026-06-18): stress penalty re-grounded (threshold 130->110 N at the matched cooperative ceiling, tanh scale 100->20 N) + PPO trust-region tightening (lr 3.0e-4->1.5e-4, clip_eps 0.2->0.1). Success predicate, f_max (130.6 N), and goal radius (0.10 m) UNCHANGED.",
  "diagnosis": "SPLIT RESULT. (1) The stress re-grounding WORKED and is DURABLE: across every checkpoint (50k-200k) the eval stress stays deep in the demonstrated cooperative band (p90 75-89 N, max 80-93 N) -- a ~40-55 N margin below the 130 N limit -- versus the budget-only incumbent that rode the edge at 132-134 N. The squeeze-fragility (the 2 on-goal/over-stress misses) is gone; stress is no longer a failure channel on any seed. (2) The PPO trust-region tightening (lr 1.5e-4, clip 0.1) did NOT stabilise the optimisation: the success-vs-frames trajectory still WANDERS (11->12->6->3 of 12; hit the 100% reference at 100k then collapsed to 25% at 200k), and the instability now expresses through TILT, which swings 46->13->21->43 deg across the same checkpoints (>15 deg limit at 50k/150k/200k). Halving the two step-size levers was insufficient; the remaining instability is in the level/tilt control, not the stress channel. Per the pre-committed rules this single reasonable-effort pass is spent: a stable, constraint-comfortable incumbent was NOT achieved, so STOP. The escalation -- warm-start the ego from the matched impedance controller (a stable basin to start in), then the residual-on-impedance architecture (learn only a bounded correction on top of the stable controller, which structurally bounds tilt/stress excursions) -- is the founder's next decision, NOT more reward/PPO tuning here.",
  "what_worked": "stress re-grounding (threshold 110 N + scale 20 N): durable, large margin below the limit on every checkpoint",
  "what_did_not": "PPO trust-region tightening (lr/clip halving): trajectory still non-monotonic (92->100->50->25%); tilt instability 13->21->43 deg",
